00:15:40.580 --> 00:15:43.200
Sengoku-kun!

00:15:43.200 --> 00:15:47.700
Violence is unacceptable!
Why did you think you could--?

00:15:48.750 --> 00:15:50.870
Is this what you were looking for?

00:15:50.870 --> 00:15:54.330
The budget files! Why do you have them?

00:15:54.330 --> 00:15:57.370
I found it in the hall yesterday.

00:15:57.370 --> 00:16:00.040
Ayasaki-san told me to throw it away.

00:16:00.040 --> 00:16:02.410
I didn't tell you to--

00:16:10.250 --> 00:16:14.080
Ohhh, you mean in the hall...

00:16:15.370 --> 00:16:20.450
Remi...

00:16:25.080 --> 00:16:28.790
I'm sorry!

00:16:28.790 --> 00:16:31.580
So it wasn't Hori-san's fault?

00:16:31.580 --> 00:16:33.200
What happened, then?

00:16:33.200 --> 00:16:35.040
Who knows?

00:16:47.450 --> 00:16:51.620
I'm just glad it got resolved.

00:16:51.620 --> 00:16:54.040
I was this close to crying.

00:16:54.040 --> 00:16:57.410
You're super organized, Hori.
No way it could've been you.

00:16:57.410 --> 00:16:59.290
Oh, c'mon.

00:16:59.290 --> 00:17:02.290
You really helped me out there, Miyamura.

00:17:02.290 --> 00:17:03.910
Thanks.

00:17:05.120 --> 00:17:06.830
I just happened to be there is all.

00:17:06.830 --> 00:17:12.330
But why'd you need to headbutt
him if you had the papers?

00:17:12.330 --> 00:17:16.500
Oh, I was just kinda pissed at him.

00:17:17.750 --> 00:17:20.870
I've been wondering, Hori-san.

00:17:20.870 --> 00:17:23.290
Does the Student Council Prez
have some dirt on you or something?

00:17:23.290 --> 00:17:24.370
Huh?!

00:17:24.370 --> 00:17:28.950
I mean, you always do
whatever he asks you to do.

00:17:28.950 --> 00:17:30.830
That <i>is </i>weird!

00:17:30.830 --> 00:17:32.040
Why do you do it?

00:17:32.040 --> 00:17:36.790
C'mon, it's just 'cause
the student council's so busy!

00:17:36.790 --> 00:17:41.790
And Sengoku... -kun and I have
known each other for forever!

00:17:41.790 --> 00:17:45.410
Sengoku, you're such a crybaby!

00:17:45.410 --> 00:17:47.910
Stop, Kyo-chan!

00:17:47.910 --> 00:17:50.540
But I <i>hate </i>peas!

00:17:50.540 --> 00:17:52.870
Rock, paper, scissors!

00:17:52.870 --> 00:17:56.450
When high school starts,
I'm not going to be your dog anymore!

00:17:56.450 --> 00:18:00.580
My <i>dog</i>? Wow, that's how you saw yourself?

00:18:00.580 --> 00:18:03.450
That's kind of hilarious.

00:18:03.450 --> 00:18:05.750
And you're going to use
an honorific with my name!

00:18:05.750 --> 00:18:08.080
I want to have a normal,
happy time in high school!

00:18:08.080 --> 00:18:09.500
Really?

00:18:09.500 --> 00:18:13.370
You'll do it, or I'll tell <i>everyone</i>
how you treated me!

00:18:13.370 --> 00:18:15.330
What, treated you <i>how</i>?

00:18:15.330 --> 00:18:17.830
Like this! This is what I'm talking about!

00:18:17.830 --> 00:18:19.080
Fine, then,

00:18:19.080 --> 00:18:21.330
S-Sen...

00:18:21.330 --> 00:18:24.870
Sengoku... -kun.

00:18:24.870 --> 00:18:29.040
That's it. Thanks, Hori-san.

00:18:32.790 --> 00:18:36.370
Seriously, I've known him forever!

00:18:36.370 --> 00:18:38.910
He definitely has dirt on her.

00:18:46.450 --> 00:18:48.250
Morning, Prez.

00:18:49.330 --> 00:18:51.830
Good morning, sir!

00:18:53.160 --> 00:18:57.040
Sengoku was traumatized by what happened.

00:19:06.580 --> 00:19:11.120
Hey, it's almost Hori's birthday.

00:19:11.120 --> 00:19:13.000
Wait, really?

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:15.120
It's at the end of March.

00:19:15.120 --> 00:19:17.870
Oh, so it's during spring break.

00:19:17.870 --> 00:19:20.870
I was thinking of getting her something.

00:19:20.870 --> 00:19:24.620
But she's turned me down once already.
I'd just be bothering her.

00:19:24.620 --> 00:19:27.000
I don't think it'd bother her.

00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:30.080
There's nothing wrong with
wanting to get her something.

00:19:30.080 --> 00:19:34.450
I guess, but I've got no idea what to get her.

00:19:34.450 --> 00:19:36.200
It's the thought that counts.

00:19:36.200 --> 00:19:39.080
Just get her whatever you want.
Maybe some jewelry or something.

00:19:39.080 --> 00:19:41.580
No way, that's way too serious.

00:19:41.580 --> 00:19:43.040
What about a desk ornament?

00:19:43.040 --> 00:19:46.620
Don't you know what kind
of stuff she likes, Miyamura?

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:50.580
A present for Hori-san...

00:19:50.580 --> 00:19:53.410
What would I give her?

00:20:05.700 --> 00:20:11.120
Hey, do you think my bro will
come here every day over break?

00:20:11.120 --> 00:20:13.660
Not every day.

00:20:13.660 --> 00:20:17.790
And remember, this won't last forever.
He'll stop coming someday.

00:20:17.790 --> 00:20:20.910
Okay... when will that be?

00:20:20.910 --> 00:20:23.330
When you graduate high school?

00:20:25.790 --> 00:20:29.700
When <i>will </i>Miyamura stop coming over?

00:20:29.700 --> 00:20:34.120
I don't know.

00:20:34.120 --> 00:20:38.660
You'd be sad if he stopped coming over, right?

00:20:38.660 --> 00:20:42.160
I'd be really sad!

00:20:42.160 --> 00:20:44.040
Hori-san.

00:20:45.160 --> 00:20:48.910
Yeah, I'd be sad!

00:20:50.080 --> 00:20:52.950
C'mon, sis, be a little
more honest with yourself.

00:20:52.950 --> 00:20:55.120
Sh-Shut it!

00:21:01.500 --> 00:21:04.500
Happy birthday!

00:21:04.500 --> 00:21:07.040
Right, it's my birthday!

00:21:07.040 --> 00:21:11.580
Spring break made me
totally forget about it. Thanks!

00:21:11.580 --> 00:21:15.040
This is from me. Happy birthday.

00:21:18.160 --> 00:21:20.250
Whoa, what is this?

00:21:20.250 --> 00:21:23.910
A CD of all the songs people
our age are into? The popular ones?!

00:21:23.910 --> 00:21:28.040
Yeah. The ones I like, at least.

00:21:28.040 --> 00:21:30.910
Thank you, Miyamura.

00:21:32.200 --> 00:21:34.750
How strange.

00:21:34.750 --> 00:21:38.910
How'd he know that this was what I wanted?

00:21:39.910 --> 00:21:41.870
You're such a weirdo.

00:21:48.370 --> 00:21:53.200
If it's my birthday, that means
spring break's almost over.

00:21:57.080 --> 00:21:58.660
Yeah.

00:22:07.410 --> 00:22:10.540
We'll be third years soon, huh?

00:23:36.620 --> 00:23:39.950 line:20%
"That's Why It's Okay"
